comments.body:
Figured out the solution: the 'hang' happens as the app is *waiting for the debugger* to connect - when "Debug - Install on device" is used, in one of the build steps, a `deploy.json` is planted somewhere on the device (e.g. /sdcard/{appId}/) where it is not affected by "Uninstall app"/"Clear data" etc*!*

Typical deploy.json:
{code:json}
    {"fastdevPort": -1, "debuggerEnabled": true, "debuggerPort": 9419, "profilerEnabled": false, "profilerPort": -1}
{code}
Quick fix for making the device usable for .apk testing again: 

Alt.1: connect the device and select Run (*not* Debug) -> Titanium Android on Device ... This should create a non-debuggy .json file 

Alt.2: open ${ANDROID_SDK_ROOT}/tools/monitor, connect to device by USB-cable, File Explorer tab, browse to the {appId} folder and manually delete `deploy.json`
